127	// applied when review-prompt synthesis runs `git show <rev>` over the
128	// evidence commit. Broader than EvidenceLandExcludePathspecs: excludes
129	// prompt.md and usage.json too, because even though they're tracked for
130	// audit, they're execution-artifact noise from the reviewer's
131	// perspective — the reviewer wants to see the implementation diff, not
132	// the prior attempt's prompt or token counters. This also protects
133	// against old commits (pre-fix) that committed the session log
134	// directly.
135	//
